org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.common

Enum SchedulerStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<SchedulerStatus>
      • org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.common.SchedulerStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<SchedulerStatus>

    @PublicAPI
public enum SchedulerStatus
extends Enum<SchedulerStatus>
implements Serializable
    Status of the scheduler. The status and what you can do with the scheduler according to the current status are best described below.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9

    • Enum Constant Summary

      UNLINKED

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • STARTED

        public static final SchedulerStatus STARTED
        The scheduler is running. Jobs can be submitted. Get the jobs results is possible. It can be paused, stopped or shutdown.

      • STOPPED

        public static final SchedulerStatus STOPPED
        The scheduler is stopped. Jobs cannot be submitted anymore. It will terminate every submitted jobs. Get the jobs results is possible. It can be started or shutdown.

      • FROZEN

        public static final SchedulerStatus FROZEN
        The scheduler is in freeze mode. It means that every running tasks will be terminated, but the pending jobs will wait for the scheduler to resume. It can be resumed, stopped, paused or shutdown.

      • PAUSED

        public static final SchedulerStatus PAUSED
        The scheduler is paused. It means that every running jobs will be terminated. It can be resumed, stopped, frozen or shutdown.

      • SHUTTING_DOWN

        public static final SchedulerStatus SHUTTING_DOWN
        The scheduler is shutting down, It will terminate all running jobs (during this time, get jobs results is possible), then it will serialize every remaining jobs results that still are in the finished queue. Finally, it will shutdown the scheduler.

      • UNLINKED

        public static final SchedulerStatus UNLINKED
        The scheduler is unlinked with RM, This can be due to the crash of the resource manager. This status will block every called to the scheduler except the terminate one and the call to reconnect to a new Resource Manager.

      • KILLED

        public static final SchedulerStatus KILLED
        The scheduler has been killed, nothing can be done anymore. (Similar to Ctrl-C)

      • DB_DOWN

        public static final SchedulerStatus DB_DOWN
        The scheduler has been killed due to a db disconnection, nothing can be done anymore.
